    • flood3D

      public FloodFill3D.FloodReport flood3D​(float[] volData, int width, int height, int depth, int[] seed, java.lang.String seedChoice, float floodMin, float floodPartMax, float floodMax, float floodVal, java.lang.String conChoice, java.lang.String testChoice)
      3D flood filler for float data
      Parameters:
      volData - A 1D representation of the 3D image horizontal raster by slice
      width - The width of the 3D image
      height - The height of the 3D image
      depth - The depth or slice count of the 3D image
      seed - An integer array of the seed location coordinates seed[0] = Column, seed[1] = Row, seed[2] = Slice
      seedChoice - A String, one of "FrontSlice","BackSlice","LeftSlice","RightSlice","TopSlice","BottomSlice","Point"
      floodMin - The minimum voxel value to flood
      floodPartMax - Voxels above this value will be flooded but counted as only partially filled
      floodMax - The maximum voxel value to flood
      floodVal - Replace voxels between floodMin and floodMax with this value. Value must not lie between floodMin and floodMax
      conChoice - A String, one of "Face","Face Edge","Face, Edge Corners"
      testChoice - A String, one of "None","Back Slice","Front Slice", "Left Side","Right Side","Top Side","Bottom Side"
      Returns:
      FloodReport
